column250: Good overall experience. Allocated 50% in each asset class then based on the last peroid's asset A mulitplier (<1 add 5% assets and >1 removed 5% assets). No

My results were not at all steady. Sometimes I would get $60  sometimes I would get less than $2. It was very irrational because I kept betting on Asset A to bring me high returns  which did not always work well.
I did not know whether or not to pay a dollar for a chance to win the 20 dollars

I chose to invest entirely in Asset A because of its higher return  on average. After my account hit certain thresholds (like 10 and 20 dollars)  I would lower the amount invested in Asset A to 20% and 10%  respectively.  |  |  | Expiriment was easy to understand. A bit long.
Went by what was the most logical investment based on previous return percentage

I was trying to maximize profits but limit the amount I would lose with investing. I was trying to be conservative at times when the variable would change to not be in my favor. It was interesting to see the trends in what was good and bad to invest in but it was usually streaks of time that would be bad or good. Overall  it was interesting to invest and try and make the best decisions when it came to managing money.

For Part 1  I made my investment decisions by safely investing in Asset B  while only investing in Asset A when I earn a lot of money. For Part 2  I made my investment decisions by totally investing in Asset B whenever I predict a bad return on Asset A  and totally investing in Asset A when I think I can get a good return. My decisions were partly based on luck  and partly by guessing what number the experiment would give to the return of Asset A because I noticed it wasn't random.

I went about my decisions as if I had money invested in the blue asset.  If the blue asset did poorly on the last multiple I would then take a small part of my "fundings out"  unless the grey asset did extremely well then I would take a majority of my fundings out (based on the bar %).  I thought this worked pretty well on average  it was a fun experiment based on luck and presumption.
I think it is good to do the experiment.
I chose what I thought would be the safest decision  and rarely took risks. I also went by a "gut"/ intuition feeling.
